{{Infobox Aircraft accident |name=1982 Garuda Fokker F28 crash |Date=20 March 1982 |Type=Runway overrun in bad weather |image=Garuda Fokker F28-1000 Volpati-1.jpg |caption= A Garuda Indonesia Fokker F28, similar to the one involved. |occurrence_type=Accident |Site=[[Radin Inten II Airport|Tanjung Karang-Branti Airport]] |Fatalities=27 |Survivors =0 |Aircraft Type=[[Fokker F28]] |Operator=[[Garuda Indonesia]] |Tail Number=PK-GVK |Passengers=23 |Crew=4 }}
The '''1982 Garuda Fokker F28 crash''' (flight number unknown) occurred on 20 March 1982, when a [[Fokker F28]], operated by [[Garuda Indonesia]], overran the runway at [[Radin Inten II Airport|Tanjung Karang-Branti Airport]] (Lampung) in the province of [[Lampung]] in [[Indonesia]] during very heavy rain.<ref name="CAA429">UK CAA Document CAA 429 World Airline Accident Summary</ref> The plane was scheduled to fly from Jakarta to Lampung.<ref>[https://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19820320-1 ASN Aircraft accident F28 March 1982 in Indonesia]</ref> The aircraft came to rest just 700 meters from the runway in a field, with the aircraft catching fire.<ref name="CAA429" /> All passengers and crew died.
==See also== * [[1979 Garuda Fokker F28 crash]], involving the same type of plane and airline. * [[Air France Flight 358]]
