{{Infobox book | name = The Legacy of Luna: The Story of a Tree, a Woman, and the Struggle to Save the Redwoods | image = Image:Legacy of luna cover.gif | image_size = 200px | author = [[Julia Butterfly Hill]] | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | publisher = [[HarperSanFrancisco]] | release_date = April 1, 2000 | media_type = Print ([[hardcover]] and [[paperback]]) | pages = 272 pp; 1st edition | isbn = 0-06-251658-2 | dewey = 333.75/16/092 B 21 | congress = SD129.H53 A3 2000 | oclc = 43115158 }}
'''''The Legacy of Luna''''' is a book written by [[Julia Butterfly Hill]] about her experiences while protecting a tree named [[Luna (Redwood Tree)|Luna]]. It is based on a true story, written like a diary of two years spent in an ancient redwood.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bluerectangle.com/book_reviews/view_one_review/2037 |title= ''The Legacy of Luna'' (review) |author= |date= |work= |publisher= |accessdate=2010-06-07}}</ref>
The book was published by HarperCollins Publishers Inc. in 2000.
==Film adaptation== A film adaptation of ''The Legacy of Luna'' called ''Luna'' was scheduled to be released in 2010{{update after|2010|12|31}}, directed by [[Deepa Mehta]]. [[Rachel Weisz]] was set to star as Hill and actively worked to get the project off the ground, saying:<ref>{{cite news | first=Mick | last=Brown | coauthors= |authorlink= | title=Rachel Weisz talks about starring in A Streetcar Named Desire | date=2009-08-01 | publisher= | url =https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/theatre/theatre-features/5931197/Rachel-Weisz-talks-about-starring-in-A-Streetcar-Named-Desire.html | work =Daily Telegraph | pages = | accessdate = 2009-09-18 | language = }}</ref>
